You are implementing a client-side pipeline run planner (`lib/client/pipeline-runner.ts`) that resolves which steps to execute when a user clicks "Run Remaining Stages" in a video production pipeline editor.

<types_ts>
<include>video_editor_pdd/lib/types.ts</include>
</types_ts>

Types
1. `PipelineRunStepId`: union of the 10 step ids: setup, tts-script, tts-render, audio-sync, specs, veo, compositions, render, stitch, audit.
2. `PipelineRunStep`: `{ id: PipelineRunStepId; label: string; stage: PipelineStage; mode: "setup" | "sse" | "job" | "sync"; endpoint: string; body?: Record<string, unknown> }`.
3. `PipelineStageStatusEntry`: `{ status: StageStatus; error?: string | null; lastJobId?: string | null; updatedAt?: string | null; stale?: boolean }`.
4. `PipelineRenderStatusSnapshot`: `{ fullVideo?: { exists: boolean; stale?: boolean; updatedAtMs?: number } }`.

Pipeline Sequence (const array, 10 steps in order)
| id | label | stage | mode | endpoint |
|----|-------|-------|------|----------|
| setup | Extract Sections | setup | setup | /api/pipeline/setup/extract-sections |
| tts-script | Generate TTS Script | tts-script | sse | /api/pipeline/tts-script/run |
| tts-render | Render Audio | tts-render | sse | /api/pipeline/tts-render/run |
| audio-sync | Run Audio Sync | audio-sync | sse | /api/pipeline/audio-sync/run |
| specs | Generate Specs | specs | sse | /api/pipeline/specs/run |
| veo | Generate Veo Clips | veo | sse | /api/pipeline/veo/run |
| compositions | Generate Compositions | compositions | sse | /api/pipeline/compositions/run |
| render | Render Sections | render | job | /api/pipeline/render/run |
| stitch | Stitch Full Video | render | sync | /api/pipeline/stitch/run |
| audit | Audit All Sections | audit | sse | /api/pipeline/audit/run |

Step Dependencies (DAG)
- setup: none
- tts-script: [setup]
- tts-render: [tts-script]
- audio-sync: [tts-render]
- specs: [tts-script, audio-sync]
- veo: [specs]
- compositions: [audio-sync, specs, veo]
- render: [compositions]
- stitch: [render]
- audit: [render]

Stage-to-Start-Step Mapping
Maps each `PipelineStage` to its starting `PipelineRunStepId`. Note: both "script" and "tts-script" map to "tts-script". All others map to the same-named step id.

Stage Labels
A `Record<PipelineStage, string>` mapping each stage to its display label (e.g., "tts-script" → "TTS Script", "audio-sync" → "Audio Sync").

Staleness Algorithm
A step's "pending reason" is one of: `done`, `not_done`, `self_stale`, `dependency_stale`. Determination:
1. **Stitch special case**: uses `renderStatus.fullVideo` — `not_done` if not exists, `self_stale` if exists but stale flag set. All other steps use `stageStatuses[step.stage]`.
2. **Self stale**: if the stage entry has `stale: true`, or if status is not "done" → `not_done`.
3. **Dependency staleness** (only checked when step is otherwise "done"): walk the dependency DAG recursively. If any dependency is `self_stale` or `dependency_stale`, mark current as `dependency_stale`. Also compare `updatedAt` timestamps — if any dependency was updated more recently than the current step, mark as `self_stale`.
4. Memoize results and guard against cycles with a visited-set.

Helper: `toTimestampMs` parses string dates via `Date.parse` or passes through finite numbers; returns `null` for invalid/missing values.

Exports
1. `resolvePipelineRunPlan(activeStage, options?)` → `PipelineRunStep[]`: Slices the sequence from the start step for the active stage. With status info, finds the first pending step and backs up through the dependency graph to the earliest required (stale) step. Returns empty array if all remaining steps are done.
2. `resolveRunRemainingButtonLabel({ activeStage, isRunning, currentStepLabel, hasError, hasRemainingSteps? })` → `string`: Returns contextual button text — running state with step label, error state with resume label using stage label, completion state, or default "Run Remaining Stages →".
3. `getPipelineAutomationDescription(activeStage)` → `string`: Returns a description of what automation will do, with special messages for "setup" (mentions extraction) and "script" (mentions setup not rerun). Default: "Runs the remaining automated stages from here and stops on the first hard error."
4. `getPipelineAutomationPlanSummary(plan)` → `string`: "Will run: label1 -> label2 -> ..." or "Nothing to run." for empty plans.
